Cross-Straits Seminar Discusses Environmental Protection
CHENGDU , September 21 ( Xinhua ) -- Scholars and ecologists from the Chinese mainland and Taiwan met today in Chengdu , the capital of Sichuan Province , to discuss ways of dealing with natural disasters in mountainous areas and improving the ecology .
The seminar is the first large scale cross-straits exchange of its kind and will have discussions , field trips , and looks at natural disasters in hilly areas , environmental protection , and flood control .
Participants are expected to look for ways to prevent disasters and work on environmental protection at the seminar , which is sponsored by China 's Society of Soil and Water Conservation .
Subsequent sessions are expected to be held alternately on the Chinese mainland and Taiwan each year .
